HEADWORD: Caboched
<hw>Ca*boched"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>caboche</ets> head. Cf. 1st <er>Cabbage</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Showing the full face, but nothing of the neck;
-- said of the head of a beast in armorial bearing.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>caboshed</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

